article.headline: Central Michigan 72, Northern Illinois 63
article.story: MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. (AP) -- Kevin Nelson tied a career high with 27 points and Giordan Watson added 15 to lead Central Michigan past Northern Illinois 72-63 on Saturday. The Chippewas (7-7, 2-4 Mid-American) held a 33-32 halftime lead despite trailing by as many as 14 points in the first half. The Huskies led for much of the first half thanks to a 17-3 run. But the Chippewas responded late in the period with a 14-0 run -- capped by a pair of Nelson 3-pointers -- to take the lead. Northern Illinois (6-8, 2-4) took the lead back early in the second half on a 10-2 run but the Chippewas stepped up their defense and held the Huskies without a field goal for over seven minutes late in the game. Meanwhile, the Chippewas built a 65-55 lead and hung on for the victory. Tom Pantlind added career-high 11 points and five rebounds for Central Michigan. Mike McKinney led the Huskies with 16 points while Anthony Maestranzi scored 13 and Cory Sims added 10. The two teams missed just four free throws in the game going a combined 29-of-33.
